sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant API as API
    participant DB as Database

    Note over C,DB: Standard Pagination Flow

    C->>API: GET /tasks/paginate?page=1&limit=20
    API->>DB: find(filters).skip(0).limit(20).count()
    DB-->>API: {data: [], total: 100}
    API-->>C: {data, total, page, totalPages}

    Note over C,DB: Aggregation Pagination Flow

    C->>API: GET /tasks/aggregate?page=1
    API->>DB: aggregate(pipeline).skip(0).limit(20)
    API->>DB: aggregate(countPipeline)
    DB-->>API: {data: [], total: 100}
    API-->>C: {data, total, page, totalPages}

    Note over C,DB: Virtual Populate Flow

    C->>API: GET /tasks/:id
    API->>DB: findById(id).populate('subtasks')
    DB-->>API: {task, subtasks: []}
    API-->>C: {task, subtasks}

    Note over C,DB: Cache-Aside Flow

    C->>API: GET /tasks/:id
    API->>Redis: GET task:id:detail
    alt Cache Hit
        Redis-->>API: cachedData
        API-->>C: cachedData
    else Cache Miss
        API->>DB: findById(id)
        DB-->>API: task
        API->>Redis: SETEX task:id:detail 300 task
        API-->>C: task
    end

    Note over C,DB: Cache Invalidation Flow

    C->>API: PUT /tasks/:id
    API->>DB: updateOne(id, update)
    API->>Redis: DEL task:id:detail
    Redis-->>API: OK
    API-->>C: updatedTask
